The [[2020 United States census]] reported that Lake Almanor Peninsula had a population of 366. The population density was {{convert|120.6|PD/sqmi|PD/km2|sp=us|adj=off}}. The racial makeup of Lake Almanor Peninsula was 324 (88.5%) [[White Americans|White]], 2 (0.5%) [[African Americans|African American]], 1 (0.3%) [[Native Americans in the United States|Native American]], 7 (1.9%) [[Asian Americans|Asian]], 2 (0.5%) [[Pacific Islander Americans|Pacific Islander]], 4 (1.1%) from [[Race (United States Census)|other races]], and 26 (7.1%) from two or more races. [[Hispanic and Latino Americans|Hispanic or Latino]] of any race were 19 persons (5.2%).<ref name=DP1>{{cite web |title=Lake Almanor Peninsula CDP, California; DP1: Profile of General Population and Housing Characteristics - 2020 Census of Population and Housing |url=https://data.census.gov/table/DECENNIALDP2020.DP1?g=1600000US0639420 |website=US Census Bureau |access-date=May 23, 2025}}</ref>

The whole population lived in households.    There were 182 households, out of which 40 (22.0%) had children under the age of 18 living in them, 113 (62.1%) were married-couple households, 11 (6.0%) were [[cohabitation|cohabiting]] couple households, 34 (18.7%) had a female householder with no partner present, and 24 (13.2%) had a male householder with no partner present. 40 households (22.0%) were one person, and 23 (12.6%) were one person aged 65 or older. The average household size was 2.01.<ref name=DP1/> There were 133 [[family (U.S. Census)|families]] (73.1% of all households).<ref>{{cite web |title=Lake Almanor Peninsula CDP, California; P16: Household Type - 2020 Census of Population and Housing |url=https://data.census.gov/table/DECENNIALDHC2020.P16?g=1600000US0639420 |website=US Census Bureau |access-date=May 23, 2025}}</ref>

The age distribution was 41 people (11.2%) under the age of 18, 23 people (6.3%) aged 18 to 24, 65 people (17.8%) aged 25 to 44, 96 people (26.2%) aged 45 to 64, and 141 people (38.5%) who were 65{{nbsp}}years of age or older. The median age was 57.3{{nbsp}}years. For every 100 females, there were 116.6 males.<ref name=DP1/>

There were 597 housing units at an average density of {{convert|196.6|/mi2|/km2|disp=preunit|units&nbsp;|units|}}, of which 182 (30.5%) were occupied. Of these, 141 (77.5%) were owner-occupied, and 41 (22.5%) were occupied by renters.<ref name=DP1/>

===2010===
The [[2010 United States census]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.census.gov/2010census/popmap/ipmtext.php?fl=06:0639420|archive-url=https://archive.today/20140715030355/http://www.census.gov/2010census/popmap/ipmtext.php?fl=06:0639420|url-status=dead|archive-date=July 15, 2014|title=2010 Census Interactive Population Search: CA - Lake Almanor Peninsula CDP|publisher=U.S. Census Bureau|accessdate=July 12, 2014}}</ref> reported that Lake Almanor Peninsula had a population of 356. The population density was {{convert|117.3|PD/sqmi|PD/km2|sp=us|adj=off}}. The racial makeup of Lake Almanor Peninsula was 337 (94.7%) [[White (U.S. Census)|White]], 0 (0.0%) [[African American (U.S. Census)|African American]], 9 (2.5%) [[Native American (U.S. Census)|Native American]], 0 (0.0%) [[Asian (U.S. Census)|Asian]], 0 (0.0%) [[Pacific Islander (U.S. Census)|Pacific Islander]], 4 (1.1%) from [[Race (United States Census)|other races]], and 6 (1.7%) from two or more races.  [[Hispanic (U.S. Census)|Hispanic]] or [[Latino (U.S. Census)|Latino]] of any race were 22 persons (6.2%).

The Census reported that 356 people (100% of the population) lived in households, 0 (0%) lived in non-institutionalized group quarters, and 0 (0%) were institutionalized.

There were 165 households, out of which 32 (19.4%) had children under the age of 18 living in them, 95 (57.6%) were [[marriage|opposite-sex married couples]] living together, 10 (6.1%) had a female householder with no husband present, 5 (3.0%) had a male householder with no wife present.  There were 6 (3.6%) [[POSSLQ|unmarried opposite-sex partnerships]], and 0 (0%) [[same-sex partnerships|same-sex married couples or partnerships]]. 47 households (28.5%) were made up of individuals, and 18 (10.9%) had someone living alone who was 65 years of age or older. The average household size was 2.16.  There were 110 [[family (U.S. Census)|families]] (66.7% of all households); the average family size was 2.57.

The population was spread out, with 67 people (18.8%) under the age of 18, 15 people (4.2%) aged 18 to 24, 60 people (16.9%) aged 25 to 44, 130 people (36.5%) aged 45 to 64, and 84 people (23.6%) who were 65 years of age or older.  The median age was 54.3 years. For every 100 females, there were 110.7 males.  For every 100 females age 18 and over, there were 103.5 males.

There were 561 housing units at an average density of {{convert|184.8|/sqmi|/km2|sp=us|adj=off}}, of which 128 (77.6%) were owner-occupied, and 37 (22.4%) were occupied by renters. The homeowner vacancy rate was 16.3%; the rental vacancy rate was 48.6%.  264 people (74.2% of the population) lived in owner-occupied housing units and 92 people (25.8%) lived in rental housing units.

